cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on keyphrase generation for social media language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG), which makes cs.IR and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The use of neural networks for keyphrase generation also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the incorporation of latent topics in the model indicates that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could also be a relevant sub-category.
